Class DataGeneratorView.CustomizedTableModel

java.lang.Object

      de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.view.DataGeneratorView.CustomizedTableModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.table.TableModel
Enclosing class:
DataGeneratorView
private class DataGeneratorView.CustomizedTableModel
extends javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel

Customized table model to display data in a tabular fashion. When the user selects a node in the tree its attributes (facets) are loaded into the table. The loading itself is done via background tasks. If the loading has finished it is displayed immediately. At that point the data is available to get modified.

initColumnSizes

private void initColumnSizes(javax.swing.JTable table)
This method picks good column sizes. If column heads are wider than the column's cells' contents, then this size is used. Otherwise the cell's size is taken.

Parameters:
table - table to adjust the columns' sizes

updateColumnSize

private void updateColumnSize(javax.swing.JTable table,
                              int row,
                              int column)
this method is like initColumnSizes(JTable). Instead of initializing the whole table with a good column size, we just update the column size at a specific column.

This happens usually, when values change in the table we update that column to have still a good column size.

Parameters:
table - that's the table to update. It has to be updated when values change within. The update is necessary to get good column sizes again. But we update only that column where the changed had happened.
row - the row where the data changed.
column - the column to update in width to get a good display feeling.
